Text.Value: Leave.
Sure thing, chromium. I will report to the Steel Watch Foundry.
You must be dismantled and your components recycled.
Ah. The ra-gnax casement protecting your metallurgised-ised valves is burning well outside the recommended temperature. You are a highly outdated model.

EditorData.NodeContext: metallurgised-ised valves = the real phrase is 'metallurgised demono-valves,' but Gortash doesn't want people knowing this tech is hellish so this word has been scrubbed

Text.Value: Gortash isn't a genius. He's just a clever arsehole.
Yeah, I'm so lucky.
Do not tarry, Steel Watcher. By order of Lord Gortash.
Why should I report to the Steel Watch factory?
Believe it or not, I'm not a Steel Watcher.
Revise your tone, citizen. Lord Enver Gortash's efforts have kept this city safe from the Absolute.
Indeed.
I guess that kind of makes us cousins.
You must report to the Steel Watch Foundry.
What if I told you I'm not a Steel Watcher?
Now report to the Steel Watch Foundry for immediate dismantling. You may not be a Steel Watcher, but you are dangerously unstable.
Your malfunction might cause him grievous bodily injury. You must report to the Steel Watch Foundry.
You are a beneficiary of the genius of Lord Enver Gortash.
This is possible but immaterial. Your composition resonates with our own.
You are indeed. Lord Enver Gortash is a blessing upon this city.
I'm here on business with Lord Gortash.
Steel Watcher. You are away from your post. Explain.
I guess that kind of makes us cousins.
If I report to this foundry, can my engine be fixed?
Your make is very obsolete. Repairing your engine would be not only impractical, but impossible.
If I report to this foundry, can my engine be fixed?

Synopsis: Karlach encounters a steel watcher and it thinks she is one of them because of her infernal engine.
